docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As House members raced to the exits for an overdue summer break in August 2007, I bumped into Representative Louise M. Slaughter in the Capitol Rotunda. I asked if she had big recess plans to wind down from her hectic first months as chairwoman of the Rules Committee after the Democratic takeover of the House that January.

headline.main: Louise Slaughter Set House Rules, and Played by Her Own
headline.print_headline: New York Lawmaker Who Set House Rules and Played by Her Own
